&lt;li&gt;And more…&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Critical Mass, we value our employees and offer competitive compensation and benefits packages. If you’re looking for a challenging and rewarding opportunity to make a significant impact on the lives of our employees, we encourage you to apply for this exciting position today!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Talent Team at Critical Mass is focused on ensuring we provide the best training, onboarding, and employee experience possible! Our new hires &amp;amp; employees are the future of our organization, and we want to set you up for long-term success. In an effort to do so, we expect our team to &lt;strong&gt;work from an office a minimum of 3 days a week&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ask Stems From Our Want To&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Strengthen opportunity for continuous learning&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Improve collaboration and team relationships.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Increase employee engagement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This work model balances the need for individual flexibility while maintaining the relentless customer fo

&lt;p&gt;The Content Author Lead (CAL) is responsible for designing templates and components, performing peer reviews, developing technical documentation and becomes a key contributor in their team and project. A Content Author Lead acts as a technical leader in projects, ensuring that the team maintains high levels of performance, and builds and strengthens the relationship with the client. The CAL will work closely with clients, developers, system administrators, project managers, business analysts and end users.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;_9538faaf _1961f02b beeb8152&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debugs or troubleshoots complex or critical issues that cannot be handled by junior positions and provides root cause analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owns content release activities, including but not limited to reviewing code changes, client demos, QA hand-offs, and presenting solutions and justifications for tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and enforce guidelines and best practices for the designated team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helps coordinate the team’s technical communication with other groups such as Creative, Business and Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible to setup regular one-on-one meetings to provide coaching, feedback, career development, and status reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overview peer reviewing and unit testing practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gathers new user and business requirements, maps them to appropriate technical solutions and estimates the associated authoring tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In charge of presentations to clients, directly working with other groups such as Creative, Business and Technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures concise and clear documentation is maintained by all peers for the projects as dictated by each Capability’s guidelines and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creates training programs for technologies within fields of expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participates in Capability activities and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a web content lead in a project and point of contact for other members of the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be involved in the recruiting process and perform interviews when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate actively in client meetings and technical discussions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Have&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;_9538faaf _1961f02b beeb8152&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 6 years of experience working with AEM, along with leadership experience guiding teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ideal candidate has a solid understanding of front-end technologies (HTML, CSS, JS) and experience applying SEO best practices to optimize content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills are very important especially when it comes to debugging, troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience automating or improving processes to boost efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who genuinely enjoys mentoring others, building strong cross-functional relationships, and fostering open communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with change, proactive mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and solution-oriented person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with data transfer formats and protocols popular in web applications (e.g. JSON, XML, HTTP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of popular JavaScript frameworks and cross-browser compatibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Front-End technologies (HTML/CSS/JavaScript).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of pre-processed CSS styling (SASS, LESS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work experience implementing SEO guidelines and best practices to CMS pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience troubleshooting, debugging and doing root cause analysis of web platform issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of designing and choosing a quality assurance process for the p

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Front-End Developer (FED) is responsible for completing front-end tasks and providing support to AEM web applications. The FED is able to work independently in basic tasks, assuming ownership for the design and programming required. For more complex work, this individual will rely on existing designs and seek guidance from more senior team members. The FED should also be able to provide constant progress status to a senior level as needed and estimates for his tasks, that must be approved by his senior or technology lead of the current project. A FED works with web applications and a variety of front-end technologies including HTML5, JavaScript and CSS. You Will&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate in implementing data exchange between application layers and AEM components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Delivery, Creative/UX, Analytics/SEO, Business, Technology, and QA teams to ensure quality and timely web development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate graphical designs and wireframes into fully styled markup code for AEM components (Touch UI Dialog, HTL/Sightly, HTML, JavaScript, and CSS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement technical solutions following the Capability&#39;s best practices and AEM design patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug or troubleshoot issues in existing web applications and provide solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide constructive feedback on operational processes (e.g., development/QA, Release etc.) when opportunities for improvement are identified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure concise and clear documentation is maintained for all projects as dictated by each Capability&#39;s guidelines and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide accurate status updates and task estimates to senior team members in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of assigned tasks and work independently while knowing when to escalate or seek guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of new technical skills, knowledge, and capabilities that can benefit project, team and personal performance&lt;/li&gt;
